==English==
===Etymology===
Coined by [[w:Carolus Linnaeus the Younger|Carolus Linnaeus the Younger]] in 1782 named after English [[botanist]] [[w:Joseph Banks|Joseph Banks]] who collected the first [[specimen]]s of the genus on his 1770 [[voyage]] to Australia with [[w:James Cook|Captain James Cook]].

J. R. Frost and G. Frost had previously, in 1775, proposed ''Banksia'' for the genus now called ''[[Pimelia]]'', but Linnaeus' use was accepted.  (Reference: [[w:Banksia#Taxonomy|wikipedia article]].)

===Proper noun===
